        "description": "A three-level mesh refinement study was performed (coarse: 1.2M cells, medium: 3.8M cells, fine: 9.6M cells) using the Grid Convergence Index (GCI) method per ASME V&V 20. GCI for the hemolysis index QoI was 2.3% between medium and fine meshes, confirming grid-independent results. The medium mesh (3.8M cells) was selected for production runs. Gradation 3 requires a formal GCI-based convergence study — exceeded."
