        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test conditions Gradation 2 — in-vitro hemolysis protocol",
        "description": "In-vitro hemolysis experiments were conducted using bovine blood at 37°C with hematocrit 33±2%, following ASTM F1841 protocol. Flow rates (2–6 L/min) and rotational speeds (2000–3500 RPM) match the five CFD operating points. Measurement uncertainty for plasma-free hemoglobin is ±5% (95% CI). Gradation 2 requires documented experimental conditions with uncertainty estimates — satisfied."
