        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Output comparison Gradation 2 — hemolysis index agreement",
        "description": "The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) predicted by CFD agrees with experimental measurements within 15% across all five operating points (mean absolute error 8.3%). The relative hemolysis index RH < 1.0 for all comparator configurations, satisfying the primary acceptance criterion. Gradation 2 requires quantitative comparison with defined tolerance — met."
