        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Validation relevance Gradation 2 — COU alignment",
        "description": "Validation experiments were conducted on the same FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry under the same five flow-speed operating points as the COU. Blood analog fluid properties (viscosity, density) match clinical CPB conditions within 5%. Gradation 2 requires that validation activities be conducted under conditions representative of the COU — satisfied by geometry and operating condition fidelity."
