        "description": "All simulations were run to iterative convergence with residuals below 1e-5 for continuity, momentum, and turbulence equations. Time-averaged quantities were computed over the final 3 impeller revolutions after initial transient decay. Gradation 2 requires documented convergence criteria and confirmation of satisfaction — met for all production simulation cases."
      },
      "rationale": "Residual convergence below 1e-5 for all governing equations is documented for every production run, satisfying Gradation 2 solver error requirements."
