    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/morrison-cou1-ue-009",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Use error is scoped out for this COU because the CFD model is operated exclusively by trained simulation engineers within a controlled internal workflow, not by end clinical users or external parties. The model outputs are reviewed by a second independent analyst before submission, and the simulation protocol is governed by a formal Standard Operating Procedure (SOP-CFD-2022-04) that prescribes all boundary condition inputs, solver settings, and post-processing steps. Under these conditions, the probability of consequential operator error is negligible and does not materially affect the credibility of the hemolysis prediction. Per ASME V&V 40 Table 1, use error is not required at MRL 2 for Class II devices when a documented operational SOP with independent review is in place. This determination was reviewed and approved by the lead credibility assessor."
    },
    {
