        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/morrison-cou1-eip-ac-013",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Equivalency of input parameters Gradation 2 — COU vs. validation conditions",
        "description": "A parameter equivalency table maps each COU input parameter to the corresponding validation experiment parameter, documenting agreement or justified differences. Flow rates, rotational speeds, fluid properties, and geometric dimensions are equivalent within stated tolerances. No COU operating condition falls outside the validated parameter space. Gradation 2 requires a documented mapping of COU inputs to validation inputs with justification of any differences — satisfied."
      },
      "rationale": "All COU input parameters are within the validated parameter space, with a documented equivalency table confirming parameter alignment at Gradation 2."
